In these Chapter Acts are also several important con- stitutions ior the regulation oi the staff oi the Minster, ior some parochial chapelrieS, and for chantries, pro- testations oi residence made by canons foundations of chantries, visitations, etc. In 1401 astatute was enacted ior the obsequies oi King Athelstan and other kingS, . archbishops oi York, and canons of Ripon, the town crier was to go round, and ‘the sanctuary men were to attend at the services. In 1505 the Chapter write to ung nenry vn offering participandi in au then rengious offices, and promising special prayers ior his weliare both in this life andin the liie to come. In 1517 was executed an indenture ior the making oi a George and Dragon according to one at Crystall (Kirkstall) Abbey, registered in Chapter in 1518. In the Chapter Acts are included also copies oi several wills proved before the Chapter. These are ior the most part oi the usual kind, but those oi William de Dalton, Canon, 1371, and oi William Cawood, another canon, 1419-20, are very long and most interesting. There is a short extract from the latter will in “ Test. Ebor.,'' I, 395.

The portion oi a cartulary referred to above extends from p. 36 to p. 98 in the present volume, and all the charters entered possess considerable local interest; the dates ascertained range from 1114 to 1322. Local research might do much to identiiy the less-known places mentioned, and the succession oi the tenuras, but the present editor has no opportunity ior an investigation oi that description, 'and can only put the matter into an accessible form, ready ior such as shall hereaiter study or write upon that portion oi Yorkshire county history which belongs to Ripon.
